{
  "id": "sages_counsel",
  "encounterTitle": "The Sage's Counsel",
  "description": "A wandering sage rests within the old northern sanctum, carrying wisdom from distant lands. Cross the open ruins to seek their counsel.",
  "mapId": "ruins",
  "npcIds": [
    "wanderer"
  ],
  "objective": "Reach the sage in the northern sanctum and hear them out",
  "customIntroduction": "The ruins stretch out before you under an open sky. Collapsed towers and a crumbling central hall stand between you and the northern sanctum, where a lone figure sits in quiet contemplation. The wandering sage has made camp here, far from prying ears.",
  "customContext": "Social encounter in an outdoor ruin. The player approaches from the south across open rubble-strewn ground. The sage (wanderer NPC) is seated inside the northern sanctum — a partially intact stone chamber at the far north of the ruins. The setting is isolated and peaceful; no enemies are present. The sage is knowledgeable, enigmatic, and willing to talk, but expects the player to make the journey across the ruins to reach them. CHAPTER COMPLETION — Once the player has reached the sage and the sage has given them their counsel (a piece of guidance, a riddle answered, a question resolved), call set_world_flag with name \"sage_counsel_received\" and value true to mark the chapter (and the adventure, if this is the final chapter) complete in adventure mode. The conversation can continue afterwards; the flag just signals that the meaningful business of the encounter is done.",
